DTSTART:20260421T153000Z
DTEND:20260421T163000Z
LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART
GEO:39.169144;-86.519739
SUMMARY:In Front of the Work: A Gallery Dialogue
DESCRIPTION:Rhonda and Anthony Moravec Gallery\, Center for Prints\, Draw
 ings\, and Photographs\, Third Floor  In this hour-long gallery conversat
 ion\, each guest brings their own perspective to the work and opens up ne
 w ways of seeing it together.  Featured guests:Beth Buggenhagen is a Prof
 essor of Anthropology at Indiana University. She writes about visual cult
 ure\, value\, gender\, and Islam in contemporary West Africa\, and is the
  author of The Future is in Your Hands: Portrait Photography from Senegal
 . Her research draws on long-term ethnographic work in Senegal and spans 
 photography\, material culture\, and global circulation.Leticia Pardo is 
 an Assistant Professor of Architecture at Indiana University's Eskenazi S
 chool of Art\, Architecture + Design. She is an architectural designer an
 d multidisciplinary artist whose work explores how place making\, migrati
 on\, and borders inform our built environments. She previously served as 
 Creative Director of Exhibition Design at the Art Institute of Chicago.  
 Facilitated by Leila Reichert\, Curator of Contemporary Art and Laura Sch
 eper\, Interpretation and Volunteer Experiences Manager.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p class="font-claude-response-body break-wo
 rds whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">  Rhonda and Anthony Moravec Gallery
 \, Center for Prints\, Drawings\, and Photographs\, Third Floor</p><p cla
 ss="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]
 ">  In this hour-long gallery conversation\, each guest brings their own 
 perspective to the work and opens up new ways of seeing it together.</p><
 p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-
 [1.7]">  Featured guests:</p><p class="font-claude-response-body break-wo
 rds whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Beth Buggenhagen</strong> is
  a Professor of Anthropology at Indiana University. She writes about visu
 al culture\, value\, gender\, and Islam in contemporary West Africa\, and
  is the author of <em>The Future is in Your Hands: Portrait Photography f
 rom Senegal</em>. Her research draws on long-term ethnographic work in Se
 negal and spans photography\, material culture\, and global circulation.<
 /p><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal lead
 ing-[1.7]"><strong>Leticia Pardo</strong> is an Assistant Professor of Ar
 chitecture at Indiana University's Eskenazi School of Art\, Architecture 
 + Design. She is an architectural designer and multidisciplinary artist w
 hose work explores how place making\, migration\, and borders inform our 
 built environments. She previously served as Creative Director of Exhibit
 ion Design at the Art Institute of Chicago.</p><p class="font-claude-resp
 onse-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">  Facilitated by L
 eila Reichert\, Curator of Contemporary Art and Laura Scheper\, Interpret
 ation and Volunteer Experiences Manager.</p>
