LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART - Room Number: Check in o
 n the first floor
SUMMARY:Writing in the Galleries
DESCRIPTION:In this workshop\, we begin by looking closely at artworkŌĆöa
 sking what we see\, think\, feel\, and wonder. Together\, we'll explore t
 he artist's possible message and its social meaning\, then turn those ref
 lections into our own creative responses.  Whether you're a writer or sim
 ply curious to try something new\, you'll find inspiration here and a wel
 coming community to share the journey.  What to Bringyour favorite pencil
  (no pens).  a notebook or paper. Clipboards are available to borrow.  a 
 phone or camera to take a picture of the art for later reference.  Know B
 efore You GoArrive early\, check in\, and get ready for an on-time start.
 Readwhere to find us\, where to park\, accessibility\, and museum guideli
 nes.About Your Facilitator  Dedaimia Whitney earned an MFA in fiction fro
 m Indiana University under the direction of Scott Russell Sanders. She ta
 ught creative writing at Franklin College for many years. She has served 
 the museum as a docent since 2019. Her favorite works of art are those th
 at are both visually stimulating and thought-provoking.
