 >Supplies</strong></h3><ul><li>Bring your favorite drawing pencil (e.g. 4
 B)\, a sketchbook or drawing paper\, and a phone or device to photograph 
 artwork (without flash) as we sketch.  </li></ul><h3><strong>Know Before 
 You Go</strong></h3><ul><li>Arrive early to find parking\, check in\, and
  get your drawing supplies ready.  </li><li>At 1:55 p.m. any unclaimed re
 servations will be released to guests who are standing by waiting for a s
 pot.  </li><li><a href="https://artmuseum.indiana.edu/visit/your-visit.ht
 ml">Where to find us\, where to park\, accessibility\, and museum guideli
 nes</a>.  </li><li>This workshop is recommended for ages 12 and up. Anyon
 e under 18\, who is not an IU student\, must be accompanied by an adult. 
  </li></ul><h3><strong>When You Arrive</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Check
  in with Guest Services at the information desk on the first floor\, even
  if you come often and even if you are late.</strong> We appreciate havin
 g an accurate attendance count.  </li><li><strong>Store all backpacks and
  large bags before entering the galleries.</strong> A small handbag may b
 e carried at your side.  </li><li><strong>Get your supplies ready.</stron
 g> Attach an 18x24" piece of newsprint to a drawing board.  </li></ul><h3
 ><strong>Cancellations</strong></h3><p>  This workshop often has a waitli
 st. Please use the cancellation link included with your confirmation emai
