SUMMARY:Stream to Studio: Exploring Local Waters and Artistic Expression 
 with Mulyana
DESCRIPTION:Participants will begin with a visit to Mulyana: Vital Ecosys
 tems\, drawing inspiration from the exhibition's imaginative underwater w
 orlds. The group will then explore a campus stream to learn how freshwate
 r macroinvertebrates help scientists assess stream health. The program co
 ncludes back at the museum with handsŌĆæon artmaking\, inspired by the bi
 odiversity observed in the stream and the visual language of the exhibiti
 on.  The program is free and open to all ages. Participants will meet at 
 the blue benches by the main museum entrance at the start of the program.
   Please dress for the weather\; jackets and boots are recommended for th
 ose who would like to step into the stream. In the event of inclement wea
 ther\, outdoor activities will shift to an indoor program.&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Participants will begin with a visit to
  <a href="https://artmuseum.indiana.edu/exhibitions/current/_feature-exhi
 bitions/2026-02-07-mulyana-vital-ecosystems.html" target="_blank" rel="no
 opener"><em>Mulyana: Vital Ecosystems</em></a>\, drawing inspiration from
  the exhibition's imaginative underwater worlds. The group will then expl
 ore a campus stream to learn how freshwater macroinvertebrates help scien
 tists assess stream health. The program concludes back at the museum with
  handsŌĆæon artmaking\, inspired by the biodiversity observed in the stre
 am and the visual language of the exhibition.</p><p>  The program is free
  and open to all ages. Participants will meet at the blue benches by the 
 main museum entrance at the start of the program.</p><p>  Please dress fo
 r the weather\; jackets and boots are recommended for those who would lik
 e to step into the stream. In the event of inclement weather\, outdoor ac
 tivities will shift to an indoor program.&#160\;</p>
