SUMMARY:Featured Exhibitions Tour
DESCRIPTION:Explore an imaginative\, immersive installation that transfor
 ms the museum into a vibrant\, crocheted\, underwater ecosystem inspired 
 by Indonesia's spectacular coral reefs. Explore colorful coral reefs\, pl
 ayful fish\, and fantastical sea creatures ŌĆö all meticulously hand-knit
  and crocheted. Read more about this featured exhibition. (https://artmus
 eum.indiana.edu/exhibitions/current/_feature-exhibitions/2026-02-07-mulya
 na-vital-ecosystems.html)Step into the world of acclaimed photographer Ra
 nia Matar (b. 1964\, Lebanon)\, whose striking portraits document young w
 omen persisting in uncertain times. Matar's lens highlights women's creat
 ivity\, strength\, dignity\, and resilienceŌĆöoffering a powerful counter
 -narrative to the challenges of her country and region. Read more about t
 his featured exhibition (https://artmuseum.indiana.edu/exhibitions/curren
 t/_feature-exhibitions/2026-03-05-rania-matar-where-do-i-go.html).  &#160
 \;  Know Before You GoSpace is available for the first 12 people to check
  in with Guest Services on the day. Drop by the information desk on the f
 irst floor of the museum when you arrive.A small handbag may be carried a
 t your side. Backpacks and large bags will need to be stored before touri
 ng. Learn more aboutmuseum guidelines.If you park in the IMU parking lot\
 , Guest Services can validate your parking voucher for a discount.Read ab
 outwhere to find us and where to park\,
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Explore an imaginative\, immersive inst
 allation that transforms the museum into a vibrant\, crocheted\, underwat
 er ecosystem inspired by Indonesia's spectacular coral reefs. Explore col
