 raphs in a personal\, meaningful way. Leila will share the stories\, rese
 arch\, and insights behind the exhibition\, making this experience as mem
 orable as the photography itself.Know Before You GoSpace is limited to 15
  participants. RSVP to reserve a space. Walk-ins are welcome if space is 
 available. If this page says "registration has closed"\, this means that 
 registration and the waitlist have filled for this date and time.Plan to 
 arrive early to check in. At 1:25 p.m.\, any unclaimed spaces may be rele
 ased to guests who are standing by waiting for a space.Admission and tour
 s are free.A small handbag may be carried at your side. Larger bags and b
 ackpacks will need to be stored before touring.Read about where to find u
 s\, where to park\, accessibility\, and museum guidelines.When You Arrive
 Check in with Guest Services staff on the first floor.If you park in the 
 IMU parking lot\, Guest Services can validate your parking voucher for a 
 discount.Be sure to store backpacks and large bags before touring. Locker
 s and coat racks are available.Keep space (18") between yourself\, includ
 ing anything you're carrying\, and the art.
